                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Khusraw va Shīrīn</title>
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="fa">خسرو و شيرين</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Meredith-Owens 1968, page 66.</bibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Titley 1977, page 141.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="37v"/>The elders pleading before<persName>Hurmuzd</persName>on behalf of the young<persName key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n84045832 ">Khusrau</persName>.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="39v"/>
                        <persName>Shīrīn</persName>being shown the portrait of<persName key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n84045832 ">Khusrau</persName>by one of her handmaidens.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="62v"/>
                        <persName>Farhād</persName>arriving at<persName>Shīrīn</persName>'s palace. (Inscription: Written for the library of the Great Amīr, the most just, the most courageous<persName>'Alī Fārsī Barlās</persName>, may God strenghten his fortune until the day of resurrection).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="72v"/>The suicide of<persName>Farhād</persName>on<name type="place">Mt. Bisitun</name>.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="93r"/>
                        <persName>Shīrūy</persName>murdering<persName key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n84045832 ">Khusrau</persName>in bed. (Inscription round the building and door are of a Persian quatrain).</decoNote>
                  </msItem>
