                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Laylá va Majnūn</title>
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="fa">ليلى ومجنون</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Meredith-Owens 1968, page 66.</bibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Titley 1977, page 141.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="106v"/>
                        <persName>Lailā</persName>and<persName>Majnūn</persName>at school. (Inscription over the doorway and below the dome are of Ḳuranic texts).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="128v"/>
                        <persName>Majnūn</persName>visited by<persName>Salīm</persName>in the desert.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="135v"/>Mourning the death of<persName>Lailā</persName>'s husband,<persName>Ibn Salām</persName>.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="137v"/>
                        <persName>Lailā</persName>and<persName>Majnūn</persName>fainting.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="144v"/>The death of<persName>Majnūn</persName>on<persName>Lailā</persName>'s grave.</decoNote>
                  </msItem>
