                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Haft paykar</title>
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="fa">هفت پيكر</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Meredith-Owens 1968, page 66.</bibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Titley 1977, page 141.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="154v"/>The building of the palace of<name type="place">Khavarnaḳ</name>for<persName>Na'mān</persName>who was the guardian of the young<persName key="http://lccn.loc.gov/nr98001026">Bahrām Gūr</persName>.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <persName key="http://lccn.loc.gov/nr98001026">Bahrām Gūr</persName>killing the dragon.<locus n="157r"/>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="175r"/>
                        <persName>Bishr</persName>feeling for the body of his drowned companion<persName>Malīkhā</persName>with a branch. (Story told by a Tartar Princess).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="190r"/>The owner of the garden discovering maidens bathing in his pool. (Story told by the Greek Princess).</decoNote>
                  </msItem>
